Sure, with some discipline you can learn to wait. But at what cost? Aside from the other drawbacks I mentioned above, don't forget boredom. Having done plenty of those Arena raids, many just for faction hits, some raids can be boring and repetitious. Add in that you have to stand looking at a giant's feet for 30 seconds before you can attack it, and you're probably about ready to fall asleep. It's poor for morale, and it can cause you to lose focus, which in itself can be dangerous.<br>
