<br>
Nice...  I guess that helps this discussion...how?<br>
<br>
Are you saying people can't stand and wait for 30 seconds before engaging a mob that a warrior is trying to get agro on because of psychiatric disorder?<br>
<br>
Or is it that people don't want to spend a chunk of their raiding time standing around next to a mob and not attacking because of warrior agro issues, when a knight class can get them into the fight quickly?<br>
<br>
Of course, I don't mean everyone - surely I'm not in this class. I know my role and I know it well.  But having played a warrior MT in more raids than I can count, and personally getting frustrated as people did this, the difference between knight classes and warrior classes are just too large to be balanced.  There's tons of great info (and a fair bit of whining) over at Steel Warriors about this issue, so my little 2cp isn't newsworthy.  <br>
<br>
Still, I find it amazing that people still fail to admit that there's even a problem with warriors.<br>
